palms up.

13
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:49,024
Raise you arms...
- Washed your feet?

14
00:02:52,465 --> 00:02:55,906
I can tell.
Makes a difference for the driver.

15
00:02:58,746 --> 00:03:00,227
What about the ears?

16
00:03:01,907 --> 00:03:03,587
You always forget something.

17
00:03:04,587 --> 00:03:08,628
Those sails must not be neglected.

18
00:03:09,349 --> 00:03:11,029
Yesterday's load was cement.

19
00:03:12,189 --> 00:03:14,909
If it rains,
concrete'll set behind you ears.

20
00:03:15,589 --> 00:03:17,469
They'll have to chisel it off.

21
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,990
You should've been born a horse.

22
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:25,910
But the Lord changed his mind.

23
00:03:32,472 --> 00:03:37,433
Beneath him the beautiful distant places
lie,

24
00:03:38,913 --> 00:03:42,473
round which the mountains darkly rise.

25
00:03:43,273 --> 00:03:45,794
By woods encircled all around.

26
00:03:48,074 --> 00:03:52,634
Amidst the flower-spattered ground.
The bright lake sleeps in slumber sound.

27
00:03:53,874 --> 00:03:56,516
The waters rippling
to its shores're striving to meet.

28
00:03:57,236 --> 00:04:00,876
Until at last
they marge in one luminous sheet.

29
00:04:00,956 --> 00:04:05,917
Only the turtle-dove does not coo forth
its call to love anymore.

30
00:04:11,998 --> 00:04:13,999
Don't shit yourself, cardboard dude!

31
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:17,518
Take these for your ears.

32
00:04:19,038 --> 00:04:22,519
If you wear them, the ears'll stick
to your head beautifully.

33
00:04:51,284 --> 00:04:55,724
A pine grove rustles on the lake's
still shore,

34
00:04:56,004 --> 00:05:00,966
Whence glorious psalm of speckled thrush
ascends.

35
00:05:02,286 --> 00:05:05,966
A portly tree stands on the rock -
an old eak.

36
00:05:06,926 --> 00:05:10,848
Through the green vale scattering
the blossoms white,

37
00:05:11,168 --> 00:05:14,408
Guding the wild geese over the woods
in flight.

38
00:05:19,368 --> 00:05:21,128
Aren't you cold?

39
00:05:21,248 --> 00:05:23,929
- I am, but nobody wants to warm me up.

40
00:05:24,089 --> 00:05:27,169
- Why dodn't you say something?
- You're a right one, eh?

41
00:05:27,449 --> 00:05:30,410
You're all smoke and no fire.
See you.

42
00:06:04,615 --> 00:06:06,176
Living it up, eh?

43
00:06:06,376 --> 00:06:09,056
- I wish!
My wife had a boy yesterday.

44
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:11,336
We celebrated a little.

45
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:14,217
- Are redheads celebrated too?
I'm surprised.

46
00:06:16,097 --> 00:06:18,457
- What's up?
- A little celebration.

47
00:06:18,937 --> 00:06:21,137
Celebrate, with your work!

48
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:53,223
- Your mate!

49
00:07:03,265 --> 00:07:05,105
- I didn't see him over there.

50
00:07:11,426 --> 00:07:13,985
- Look at him!
Look at the nitwit!

51
00:07:20,747 --> 00:07:24,947
That... that...
If it was stone, you'd've been dead!

52
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:26,707
You...
An animal has more brains!

53
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:30,189
You oaf!

54
00:07:34,309 --> 00:07:38,429
Gone's the furor of that Age
which Time bore far away.

55
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:43,870
Far-far off even its dream -
as a shadow did it fade,

56
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:48,351
As the image of white citiens
in the waters'depths arrayed,

57
00:07:48,991 --> 00:07:52,432
